  ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & MACHINE LEARNING
============================================================

Concept:     Fine-tuning
Category:    Training technique
Definition:  Updates pre-trained model weights on task-specific data
Year:        2018
Researchers: Howard/Ruder (ULMFiT)
Applications:Customizing LLMs, domain adaptation
Related:     Supervised fine-tuning, PEFT, LoRA

Concept:     Transfer Learning
Category:    Technique
Definition:  Reuses pre-trained model weights for new related tasks
Year:        2009
Researchers: Pan and Yang survey
Applications:Fine-tuning LLMs, computer vision
Related:     Pre-training, fine-tuning, domain adaptation

Concept:     Reinforcement Learning
Category:    Paradigm
Definition:  Agent learns from environment interaction to maximize reward
Year:        1950
Researchers: Bellman; Sutton/Barto
Applications:Games, robotics, recommendations, LLM alignment
Related:     Reward, policy, value function, Q-learning

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Central Limit Theorem
Branch:       Statistics
Formula:      Sample means approach normal distribution
Applications: Polling, quality control, finance
Discoverer:   Lyapunov (1901)

Theorem/Law:  Quadratic Formula
Branch:       Algebra
Formula:      x = (-b ± sqrt(b²-4ac))/2a
Applications: Engineering, physics
Discoverer:   Ancient Babylonians (2000)

Theorem/Law:  Bayes Theorem
Branch:       Probability
Formula:      P(H|E) = P(E|H)P(H)/P(E)
Applications: ML, spam filters, medical testing
Discoverer:   Thomas Bayes (1763)

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Phenomenology
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   Philosophy must study first-person conscious experience directly
Philosopher:  Husserl/Heidegger
Example:      What is the structure of my experience of time or other people?

Concept:      Utilitarianism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   The right action maximizes total happiness for greatest number
Philosopher:  Bentham/Mill
Example:      Sacrifice one to save five if it maximizes total utility

Concept:      Social Contract
Branch:       Political
Definition:   Legitimate authority derives from agreement among individuals
Philosopher:  Hobbes/Locke/Rousseau
Example:      People surrender freedoms to government for security and rights

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Monetarism
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Inflation caused primarily by excessive money supply growth
Formula:    MV = PQ
Economist:  Milton Friedman
Example:    Fed raising interest rates to control money supply and inflation

Concept:    Inflation
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: General rise in price levels eroding purchasing power
Formula:    Inflation = (CPI_t - CPI_t-1)/CPI_t-1 x 100
Economist:  Irving Fisher
Example:    2022 US inflation hit 9.1%; Fed raised rates to combat it

Concept:    Opportunity Cost
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Value of next-best alternative foregone when choosing
Formula:    OC = forgone alternative value
Economist:  Bastiat
Example:    Studying means forgoing wages you could have earned working

